    "# Amazon Product Intelligence System  \n",
    "## EDA + Value/Trust Scoring + Product Segmentation (Business Insights)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Project Overview  \n",
    "This project analyzes Amazon product data containing information such as product category, prices, discounts, ratings, and customer review counts.  \n",
    "The goal is to build a **Product Intelligence System** that goes beyond basic EDA by introducing:\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ **Value Score** (deal quality)  \n",
    "✅ **Trust Score** (rating reliability)  \n",
    "✅ **Popularity Score** (market demand proxy)  \n",
    "✅ **Product Segmentation** using clustering  \n",
    "\n",
    "This system helps identify:  \n",
    "- Best Deals (high value + high trust)  \n",
    "- Discount Traps (high discount but low trust)  \n",
    "- Hidden Gems (high trust but low visibility)  \n",
    "- Premium Picks (high price but trusted)  \n",
    "- Market Leaders (high popularity)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Business Problem Statement\n",
    "\n",
    "Amazon offers a wide range of products across categories with varying price levels, discounts, and customer feedback.  \n",
    "However, not all discounted products are valuable, and not all ratings are equally trustworthy.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Business Questions:\n",
    "1. Which products provide the **best value for money**?\n",
    "2. Do higher discounts lead to better customer satisfaction?\n",
    "3. Which categories show risky patterns (high discounts but low ratings)?\n",
    "4. Can we segment products into actionable groups for promotions and catalog decisions?\n",
    "\n",
    "### Expected Outcome:\n",
    "Create a system that ranks and segments products based on **value**, **trust**, and **popularity**, enabling data-driven recommendations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
