    "## 9. Product Intelligence Scoring System\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the core contribution of the project.\n",
    "\n",
    "We compute three business scores:\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1) Popularity Score (0–100)\n",
    "Represents product popularity based on rating_count (proxy for engagement).\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2) Trust Score (0–100)\n",
    "Measures reliability of ratings by using a weighted rating approach.\n",
    "This prevents products with few reviews from appearing unrealistically high.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3) Value Score (0–100)\n",
    "Captures deal attractiveness based on discount percentage + affordability.\n",
    "\n",
    "These scores convert raw data into decision-ready metrics."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 9.1 Popularity Score\n",
    "\n",
    "We normalize rating_count into a 0–100 scale to represent marketplace popularity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df[\"popularity_score\"] = (df[\"rating_count\"] - df[\"rating_count\"].min()) / (\n",
    "    df[\"rating_count\"].max() - df[\"rating_count\"].min()\n",
    ") * 100"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 9.2 Trust Score (Weighted Rating)\n",
    "\n",
    "Ratings alone can be misleading when rating_count is low.  \n",
    "We compute a weighted rating that adjusts ratings toward the global mean when votes are limited."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "m = df[\"rating_count\"].quantile(0.60)   # threshold\n",
    "C = df[\"rating\"].mean()                # overall average rating\n",
    "\n",
    "def weighted_rating(row):\n",
    "    v = row[\"rating_count\"]\n",
    "    R = row[\"rating\"]\n",
    "    return (v/(v+m))*R + (m/(v+m))*C\n",
    "\n",
    "df[\"weighted_rating\"] = df.apply(weighted_rating, axis=1)\n",
    "df[\"trust_score\"] = (df[\"weighted_rating\"] - df[\"weighted_rating\"].min()) / (\n",
    "    df[\"weighted_rating\"].max() - df[\"weighted_rating\"].min()\n",
    ") * 100"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 9.3 Value Score (Deal Quality)\n",
    "\n",
    "We combine:\n",
    "- Discount component (higher discount is better)\n",
    "- Price component (lower discounted price gives higher value)\n",
    "\n",
    "This helps identify “true deals” rather than marketing discounts."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "price_component = 1 - (df[\"discounted_price\"] - df[\"discounted_price\"].min()) / (\n",
    "    df[\"discounted_price\"].max() - df[\"discounted_price\"].min()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "discount_component = (df[\"discount_percentage\"] - df[\"discount_percentage\"].min()) / (\n",
    "    df[\"discount_percentage\"].max() - df[\"discount_percentage\"].min()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "df[\"value_score\"] = (0.6 * discount_component + 0.4 * price_component) * 100"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10. Product Segmentation (Clustering)\n",
    "\n",
    "In this step, we segment products into groups using clustering.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Features used:\n",
    "- Value Score\n",
    "- Trust Score\n",
    "- Popularity Score\n",
    "\n",
    "### Algorithm:\n",
    "K-Means clustering\n",
    "\n",
    "Segmentation allows Amazon to:\n",
    "- identify products suitable for promotions\n",
    "- detect risky products\n",
    "- boost visibility of hidden gems\n",
    "- maintain premium catalog strategy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 10.1 Prepare Data for Clustering\n",
    "\n",
    "We standardize the features to ensure equal scale impact in K-Means."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "features = df[[\"value_score\", \"trust_score\", \"popularity_score\"]].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X = scaler.fit_transform(features)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 10.2 Train K-Means Model\n",
    "\n",
    "We choose a value of K (clusters) and assign a segment label to each product."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=5, random_state=42)\n",
    "df[\"segment\"] = kmeans.fit_predict(X)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 10.3 Segment Profiling\n",
    "\n",
    "We analyze each cluster by calculating:\n",
    "- average Value Score\n",
    "- average Trust Score\n",
    "- average Popularity Score\n",
    "\n",
    "Then we assign meaningful business labels such as:\n",
    "- Best Deals\n",
    "- Discount Traps\n",
    "- Hidden Gems\n",
    "- Market Leaders\n",
    "- Premium Picks"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "segment_summary = df.groupby(\"segment\")[[\"value_score\",\"trust_score\",\"popularity_score\"]].mean().sort_values(\n",
    "    by=\"trust_score\", ascending=False\n",
    ")\n",
    "segment_summary"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# manually map after seeing segment_summary\n",
    "segment_map = {\n",
    "    0: \"Best Deals\",\n",
    "    1: \"Discount Trap\",\n",
    "    2: \"Hidden Gems\",\n",
    "    3: \"Market Leaders\",\n",
    "    4: \"Premium Picks\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "df[\"segment_name\"] = df[\"segment\"].map(segment_map)"
   ]
  },
